# MVC Structure

Keep Model–View–Controller separation on both sides. Do not dump logic into `App.jsx` or `server/index.js`.

## Server (`server/`)

| Layer | Folder | Responsibility |
|-------|--------|----------------|
| Model | `models/` | DB queries and data access |
| Controller | `controllers/` | Request handling, call models, shape responses |
| Routes | `routes/` | Wire HTTP paths to controllers only |
| Config | `config/` | DB and env setup |
| Utils | `utils/` | Shared helpers |

Flow: `routes` → `controllers` → `models`

## Client (`src/`)

| Layer | Folder | Responsibility |
|-------|--------|----------------|
| View | `views/` | Presentational UI (layout, pages, components) |
| Controller | `controllers/` | Hooks/handlers: state, events, call models |
| Model | `models/` | API calls and client data access |
| Config | `config/` | API base URL and client config |
| Utils | `utils/` | Shared helpers |

Flow: `views` → `controllers` → `models` → API

## Rules

- New features get matching files in the correct layer (e.g. `healthModel` + `healthController` + route/view).
- Views stay presentational; no `fetch` inside views.
- Controllers do not contain raw SQL or HTML markup.
- Models do not handle HTTP status codes or JSX.
- Prefer extending this layout over adding one-off folders at the root of `src/` or `server/`.
